er of Pierre Trudeau. The essays come from the University League for Social Reform, an informal group of university professors, young rather than old, to the left rather than the right, who meet together in Toronto each year to discuss some aspect of the problem of the relationship of Canadians to their society, their government, and their future. Academics interested in influencing policy, they like to think of themselves of the first wave of the drive for Ivory Power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aBlair, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrummond, Ian M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodgetts, J. E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorowitz, Gad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLloyd, Trevor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLloyd, Trevor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcLeod, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLeod, Jack, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNowlan, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Neill, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaquet, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott, F. R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilcox, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrayer, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWatkins, Mel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversit